main event: A sighting of a UFO was reported in Utica, New York on July 30, 1956.
interesting points: The UFO was reported as round with a diameter of 20 yards and was black in color., The sighting was classified as a ground-visual observation., The conclusion indicated that the sighting was probably caused by a natural phenomenon related to cloudy skies., Personnel manning the GOC post reported that the flying object disappeared when a T/T jet aircraft came into the vicinity., The report was taken from the 4585th Installation Squadron at Wright-Patterson AFB, Ohio.
